Posted @withrepost • @mrolympiallc MASTER OLYMPIA RETURNS! After an absence of 11 years, Masters Olympia returns to competitors and fans alike, with an upgrade: the 2023 edition will offer the chance to fight for the best master competitor title in the world in all 10 divisions of the IFBB Pro League! 
Date: August 25-27, 2023

Location: BTArena, Cluj Napoca, Romania

ATHLETE QUALIFICATION CRITERIA:

Age Requirements
+40 for Wellness, Bikini, Fitness, Men's Physique, Men's Classic Physique,Women's Physique, Figure.

+45 for Men's Bodybuilding, Men's 212, Women's Bodybuilding.

Participation based on individual application, please send  your letter of intent to:
mastersolympia@mrolympia.com

Application letters need to include:

-athlete background such as age, country, titles

-competitive history, including the last show the athlete took part in

-social media accounts

Optional:

-Video Application (no longer than 1 minute)

-Pictures of the athletes’ actual shape

Application Deadline: April 10, 2023

List of Invitations will be published on April 24, 2023.

Stay tuned for more details coming soon!

Posted @withregram • @mrolympiallc IT’S OFFICIAL: THE MASTERS OLYMPIA WILL MAKE HISTORY THIS AUGUST
 
The fitness industry’s most prominent event brand is preparing for another round of expansion with the return of the prestigious Masters Olympia. After an 11 year break, Olympia organizers are bringing back the Masters Olympia, but this time titles are up for grabs in 10 competitive divisions.

Scheduled for the Weekend of August 26-27, the event will take place at the spectacular BT Arena in Cluj, Romania.
Olympia President Dan Solomon explains, “The time has come to bring back this great tradition. Athletes around the world are maintaining elite condition as they age into their 40’s and beyond. We want to give them the opportunity to continue pursuing their dream of competing for a coveted Olympia title.”

. Look for more updates at MrOlympia.com

We send our sincere condolences to the family and friends of Amy Richardson. 🙏🏽

Women’s Physique bodybuilder Amy Richardson has passed away at 49 years old. In a recent Instagram post, she mentioned that she caught pneumonia and the flu while attending the 2022 Mr. Olympia Weekend. 
“Lucky me…caught pneumonia and the flu while in Vegas….double whammy. Starting to feel a little better but lost lots of my gains…time to reset and restart. Thanks to my hubby who has been taking care of me… Merry Christmas everyone!,”
 Amy shared via Instagram.

Posted @withregram • @carlos_thomasjr_ Hey everyone,

I wanted to take a moment to address the fact that I won't be participating in the upcoming New York Pro show. Unfortunately, I've been dealing with some severe issues related to my ulcerative colitis that has made it impossible for my body to respond in the way that I need it to in order to compete.

As disappointed as I am that I won't be able to show off all the hard work I've put in, I'm optimistic about the future. I'm taking the time to focus on my health and well-being, and I'm confident that with the treatment plan we have in place, I’m heading in the right direction, and I’m feeling much better! 

I'm already looking forward to a later show date, and I can't wait to step on that stage and show the world what I'm capable of. In the meantime, I'm going to keep working hard, staying positive, and taking care of myself.

Thank you to @bevsgym, Big Steve, and everyone for all your support and understanding. I genuinely appreciate it. 

I will still be attending the NY Pro to show support to my fellow competitors and friends, so until then, I’ll see you guys down the road 🤙🏾

As excitement builds for Olympia Weekend, organizers of the fitness industry’s most anticipated weekend are completing the final stages of an Expo expansion, featuring the addition of several high profile events.
 
Voted one of the top convention destinations in the United States, Orlando’s Orange County Convention Center will welcome the fitness industry the first weekend in November as top brands, major celebs, and a sea of fitness enthusiasts come together for the Olympia World Fitness Expo, at the heart of Olympia Weekend.
 
Some of the featured events include the Olympia Bare Knuckle Fighting Championships, America’s Strongest Man, WPO Powerlifting, The Abu Dhabi Combat Club Submission Grappling Tournament, The Olympia Sumo Championship, Special Olympics Fit Games, America’s Strongest Woman, Olympia Ultimate Arm Wresting, Olympia World Ninja League Classic and a growing list of more than 30 events, along with the Muscle & Fitness Anti-Aging Pavilion and the preliminary judging for 10 IFBB Pro League Olympia Divisions.
 
Olympia President Dan Solomon explains, “With so much attention on the coveted Mr. Olympia title and our record prize money, we’ve decided it’s time to elevate and expand our expo experience. Trade shows around the world are enjoying a lot of momentum. It’s been fun seeing fans, exhibitors and participants showing up in big numbers to celebrate their commitment to strength, health and overall fitness. We can’t wait to see everyone in Orlando.”
 
Visit MrOlympia.com today for event tickets, expo passes and everything you need to know about the fitness industry’s most prestigious event. #Olympia23
